A man was killed by a mob after he was caught stealing a motorcycle in Athi, Igembe South, Meru County.&nbsp; According to witnesses, the man was in the company of two accomplices when they turned against a boda boda operator who they had hired. &quot;The three men accosted the rider once they reached a secluded area on the Maua-Mikinduri road. They attacked him and tried to steal the motorcycle, but people who were passing by the raised alarm,&quot; said the witness. Two suspects ran away but but their accomplice was cornered and beaten before his body was set ablaze. The owner of the motorcycle suffered stabbing injuries.